275
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:41,260
Sonny, where did you find this "S" shaped hook?

276
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:44,760
It was stuck to the metal part of this telephone pole.

277
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:49,760
I see. The scratch on the metal part of this pole is still new.

278
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:52,160
And I'm sure it's there too.

279
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:57,260
See! There's a scratch here too!

280
00:15:57,260 --> 00:16:00,460
Right on the opposite side is the sign.

281
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:04,360
Just as I thought.

282
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:05,560
I see!

283
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:10,460
There is a cut off piano cord left on the pole of this sign.

284
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:12,160
Which means...

285
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:14,960
the piano cord which stretched out from the "S" shaped hook

286
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,360
stuck to the ladder,

287
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:18,960
was wrapped around a nearby telephone pole

288
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:22,060
and hooked on to a telephone pole about to meters behind,

289
00:16:22,060 --> 00:16:23,860
then stretched over to the pole of the sign

290
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:26,660
on the opposite side of the rails.

291
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:30,560
The streetcar that came along, pulled the piano cord.

292
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:33,060
The leg of the ladder is dragged,

293
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:35,060
loses balance and falls.

294
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:38,360
The frame was thus forced to fall.

295
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,960
But who would do something like this?

296
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:42,360
This trick is too complicated to be a simple prank.

297
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:44,460
I wonder if the ladder falling

298
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:49,460
and Mr. Horii's death is connected?

299
00:16:49,460 --> 00:16:51,760
I see! That's it!

300
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:55,660
I, Officer Wakai, will solve the mystery of this case.

301
00:16:55,660 --> 00:16:58,060
Let's all go back to the streetcar.

302
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:02,160
Hey, hey. Can you work it out or what?

303
00:17:05,460 --> 00:17:08,160
Okay, everyone, are you ready?

304
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:10,460
Mr. Horii didn't die of an accident.

305
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:12,260
He was murdered!

306
00:17:12,260 --> 00:17:14,360
What?

307
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:18,360
But you just said it was an accident a while ago.

308
00:17:18,360 --> 00:17:21,560
Yes, but I've also found out that Mr. Kawasaki's ladder

309
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:24,360
was rigged by someone and made to fall.

310
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:28,460
What? You mean somebody was trying to kill me?

311
00:17:28,460 --> 00:17:31,360
Yes, maybe.

312
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:33,160
What do you mean?

313
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:36,160
You say that Mr. Horii didn't die of an accident,

314
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:38,460
and on top of that, you're saying that

315
00:17:38,460 --> 00:17:41,160
somebody deliberately made Mr. Kawasaki's ladder fall.

316
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:43,460
I'll explain that now.

317
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:46,860
First, for the way that Mr. Horii was murdered.

318
00:17:46,860 --> 00:17:51,860
If the murderer knew that the streetcar was going to stop suddenly.

319
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:54,160
Yes, if the ladder that Mr. Kawasaki was on

320
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:56,960
could be rigged to fall.

321
00:17:56,960 --> 00:18:00,760
It would be possible to kill Mr. Horii in no time at all.

322
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:03,460
Mr. Kawasaki came falling

323
00:18:03,460 --> 00:18:06,360
and your attention were all fixed on what was happening ahead.

324
00:18:07,460 --> 00:18:08,760
Taking advantage of the situation,

325
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:12,460
the killer hit the back of Mr. Horii's head with the camera case.

326
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:14,860
And Mr. Horii who fell forward,

327
00:18:14,860 --> 00:18:17,060
hit his forehead on the railing

328
00:18:17,060 --> 00:18:19,460
and fell to the floor,

329
00:18:19,460 --> 00:18:22,060
leaving a pool of blood.

330
00:18:22,860 --> 00:18:24,060
The killer immediately

331
00:18:24,060 --> 00:18:25,960
strapped the camera case back to where it was,

332
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:30,460
but being in a rush could only wrap the belt around the railing once.

333
00:18:31,660 --> 00:18:34,660
Right after that, the streetcar suddenly stopped

334
00:18:34,660 --> 00:18:36,360
that Mr. Horii's body slid

335
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:39,160
and he hit his head on the camera case.

336
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:45,460
At that time, the person who was nearest to Mr. Horii

337
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:48,060
was you, isn't that right? Ms. Shimizu!

338
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:50,660
You've gotta be kidding!

339
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:52,960
I was thrown forward when the streetcar stopped

340
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:55,060
and almost died too!

341
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:57,060
Driver.

342
00:18:57,060 --> 00:19:01,260
There was another streetcar that went by before you, right?

343
00:19:01,260 --> 00:19:05,360
It went by about 5:40 a.m.

344
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:11,560
If so, the killer rigged the piano cord after 5:40 a.m.

345
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,260
And it had to be somebody who knew that

346
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:16,560
Mr. Kawasaki was going to be taking pictures here.

347
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:21,560
Horii, Shimizu and I decided to take pictures here yesterday.

348
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:25,560
I took it there this morning before going to the station.

349
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:30,260
I was at Harii Station by 5:54 a.m.

350
